<TITLE> Head of army probe team visits BDR HQ </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 3 (bdnews24.com)  Lt Gen Md Jahangir Alam Chowdhury, who is leading the army's own inquiry into the BDR mutiny, visited the Peelkhana headquarters on Tuesday for the first time. Accompanied by senior officials, he viewed a number of key spots, including Darbar Hall, the director general's residence and the grave sites, Chowdhury told reporters afterwards. The army formed a nine-member investigation team, headed by Chowdhury, on Monday. The government recast its probe committee the same day, appointing former civil servant Anisuzzaman Khan as head to replace home minister Sahara Khatun. bdnews24.
